University Elective Course Management System ERD – Explained
Overview

This database is designed to manage a university elective course system, including academic structure, students, instructors, courses, sections, and enrollments.

Core Design Principles
Normalized design to reduce redundancy
Clear separation of academic entities
Shared person entity for students and instructors
Many-to-many relationships resolved through junction tables
Entities
University

Stores university information and acts as the top-level academic entity.

Relationship:
One university → many schools

School

Represents academic schools/faculties.

Relationship:
One school → many departments

Department

Represents subdivisions inside schools.

Relationship:
One department → many majors

Major

Represents academic programs.

Relationship:
One major → many students

Person

Stores shared personal information such as name, gender, and birthdate.

Used by:

Student
Instructor
Student

Represents enrolled students.

Relationship:
One student → many enrollments

Instructor

Represents teaching staff.

Relationship:
One instructor → many sections

Course

Represents academic courses.

Relationship:
One course → many sections

Semester

Represents academic periods.

Examples:

Fall 2025
Spring 2026

Relationship:
One semester → many sections

Section

Represents actual course offerings.

Stores:

class time
location
instructor
semester
course
Enrollment

Stores:

enrollment date
grade
status
Relationships Summary
Relationship	Type
University → School	1:M
School → Department	1:M
Department → Major	1:M
Major → Student	1:M
Person → Student	1:1
Person → Instructor	1:1
Course → Section	1:M
Semester → Section	1:M
Instructor → Section	1:M
Student ↔ Section	M:N via Enrollment
Design Decisions
Person entity avoids duplicating student/instructor personal data.
Section entity separates course definitions from actual scheduled offerings.
Enrollment table resolves the many-to-many relationship between students and sections.
Academic hierarchy organizes data clearly from university down to majors.
Notes

Current ERD may still need refinement for:
stricter business constraints
Conclusion

This ERD provides a solid foundation for a university elective course management system with a clear academic structure and scalable design.
